Hydrodec Group plc



16/09/2016 | Press release | Distributed by Public on 16/09/2016 13:05
Half Yearly Report







      Half Yearly Report
    

      Released : 16 Sep 2016 07:00
    

      RNS Number : 0057K HydroDec Group plc 16 September 2016
    

      16 September 2016
    

      Hydrodec Group plc
    

      ("Hydrodec", the "Company" or the "Group")
    

      Unaudited Interim Results
    

      Hydrodec Group plc (AIM: HYR), the clean‐tech industrial oil re‐reﬁning group, today announces unaudited results for the six months ended 30 June 2016.
    

      Financial highlights
    



          Revenues from con nuing core re‐reﬁning business increased by 148% to US$8.1 million (H1 2015: US$3.3 million), reﬂec ng full commissioning of new Canton plant at the end of 2015 and increased market penetra on
        



          H1 2016 gross unit margins in con nuing business higher than H1 2015 despite lower product sales prices and challenging market condi ons
        



          Key focus on reduc on of corporate costs in con nuing opera ons, falling from US$2.1 million (H1 2015) to US$1.5 million
        



          Group EBITDA from con nuing opera ons improved from US$3.4 million loss (H1 2015) to US$1.1 million loss ‐ expecta on of move to posi ve EBITDA in H2
        



          Overall loss for the period (including discon nued opera ons) down from US$8.4 million (H1 2015) to US$5.3 million
        



          Opera ng cash ou low (before working capital movements) reduced to US$2.0 million (H1 2015: US$5.8 million)
        

          Opera onal highlights
        



          Substan ally increased Group sales volumes of premium quality SUPERFINE transformer oil and base oil of 16.75 million litres (H1 2015: 1.7 million litres) ‐ record monthly sales in June of 3.2m litres
        



          Improving plant u lisa on ‐ Canton reaching 76% in May
        



          Con nued successful produc on in Australia and improving feedstock posi on
        



          SUPERFINE transformer oil in US achieved "500 hour" status, cer fying its quality


          Strategic highlights
        



          Appointment of new CEO with strategic focus on core transformer oil re‐reﬁning business and associated technology
        



          Disposal of loss‐making UK recycling opera ons in March
        

          Post period‐end highlights
        



          Awarded 5‐year contract for supply of transformer oil by Essen al Energy, a major Australian u lity
        



          Obtained American Carbon Registry approval for registering, and mone sing, carbon credits
        



      Chris Ellis, Chief Execu ve Oﬃcer of Hydrodec, commented: "I am pleased to be able to report signiﬁcant progress in moving Hydrodec towards proﬁtability and re‐establishing its posi on in the transformer oil market in our key opera ng arenas as we have moved Canton into full opera ons and improved eﬃciency in Australia. Whilst market condi ons and margins, par cularly in the US, remain challenging, both opera ons are genera ng posi ve EBITDA and the focus now for the rest of this year is to improve margins
    

      and proﬁtability as well as taking advantage of any opportuni es the current market may yet present to grow the business within both our exis ng pla orms and in new markets."





            For further informa on please contact:
          

            Hydrodec Group plc
          



            020 3300 1643
          





            Chris Ellis, Chief Execu ve
          





            Canaccord Genuity (Nominated Adviser and Broker)


            Henry Fitzgerald‐O'Connor Richard Andrews
          



            020 7523 8000
          





            Vigo Communica ons ( P R a d v i s e r t o Hydrodec)


            Patrick d'Ancona Chris McMahon
          



            020 7830 9700
          




      Notes to Editors:
    

      Hydrodec's technology is a proven, highly eﬃcient, oil re‐reﬁning and chemical process ini ally targeted at the mul ‐billion US$ market for transformer oil used by the world's electricity industry. MarketsandMarkets forecasts that the global transformer oil market is expected to grow from US$1.98 billion in 2015 to US$2.79 billion by 2020 at a CAGR of 7.14% from 2015 to 2020. Spent oil is currently processed at two commercial plants with dis nct compe ve advantage delivered through very high recoveries (near 100%), producing 'as new' high quality oils at compe ve cost and without environmentally harmful emissions. The process also completely eliminates PCBs, a toxic addi ve banned under interna onal regula ons. Hydrodec's plants are located at Canton, Ohio, US and Bomen, New South Wales, Australia.
    

      Hydrodec's shares are listed on the AIM Market of the London Stock Exchange. For further informa on, please visit www.hydrodec.com.
    

      The informa on contained within this announcement is deemed to cons tute inside informa on as s pulated under the Market Abuse Regula ons (EU) No. 596/2014. Upon the publica on of this announcement, this inside informa on is now considered to be in the public domain.
    

      Chief Execu ve's Report
    

      A er a par cularly diﬃcult 2015 for the Company, I am pleased to be able to report signiﬁcant progress in delivering the Company's key objec ves during the period under review, achieved against a challenging, yet improving, market backdrop.
    

      Strategy
    

      At the me of my appointment as CEO and the divestment of the UK recycling opera ons in March 2016, the Board restated its strategy to concentrate on the Group's market leading transformer oil re‐reﬁning technology and business and to grow that business to access an increasing propor on of the US$2 billion plus global transformer oil market. Speciﬁcally, the Board stated its inten on, as the Company moves forward through 2016, to look to strengthen Hydrodec's footprint in the US and in the interna onal transformer oil market, where the Board believes Hydrodec has a compe ve advantage through its proven and market‐leading technology.
    

      In line with this strategy, my focus has been to grow the transformer oil business in order to drive proﬁtability, with a rigorous focus on execu on when deploying our market leading transformer oil re‐reﬁning technology, making eﬀec ve costs savings and delivering the ramp‐up of produc on and sales in the US.
    




            Con nuing business ‐ re‐reﬁning
          

