Contract Win







      Contract Win
    

      Released : 18 Aug 2016 07:00
    

      RNS Number : 4886H HydroDec Group plc 18 August 2016
    

      18 August 2016
    

      Hydrodec Group plc
    

      ("Hydrodec" or the "Company")
    

      Long Term U lity Contract Awarded
    

      The Company is pleased to report that its Australian opera on has been awarded a 5 year contract for the supply of inhibited transformer and switchgear oil by Essen al Energy, a major Australian u lity. The contract includes the collec on and re‐reﬁning of all generated PCB and non‐PCB waste oils and is expected to generate over 1 million litres of new transformer oil sales over the life of the contract. The contract was awarded under a compe ve tender process, with the Company successfully compe ng against a range of new oil suppliers. Under this contract, Hydrodec will become the sole supplier of new inhibited transformer and switchgear oil to Essen al Energy. The Company expects to start supplying oil under the new contract from September 2016.
    

      Commen ng on this success, Chris Ellis, Chief Execu ve Oﬃcer of Hydrodec said "I am hugely encouraged by this contract award as it is a signiﬁcant milestone in the evolu on of the Company's ac vi es. Although it will only make a modest contribu on at the Group level, it is a very signiﬁcant contract both locally and strategically. We are delighted that our re‐reﬁned transformer oil was successful in a compe ve tender and exceeded the technical product acceptance criteria. It is further evidence of the quality of our product and provides the basis to develop similar rela onships with other u li es in Australia and elsewhere."
    




            For further informa on please contact:
          

            Hydrodec Group plc
          



            020 3300 1643
          





